## Partial Derivatives

### ∂Φ/∂μ (Metal Partial)
- **What changes:** Clarity of standards, criterion level, structural support
- **At μ↑:** High standards, clear objectives, well-organized system
- **At μ↓:** Vague goals, arbitrary assessment, structural confusion

### ∂Φ/∂δγ (Earth Partial)
- **What changes:** Quality of feedback, effectiveness of correctives, time allocation
- **At δγ↑:** Rich feedback, effective cycling, adequate time for all
- **At δγ↓:** Superficial feedback, ineffective correctives, rushed pacing

### ∂Φ/∂λ (Fire Partial)
- **What changes:** Student persistence, motivation, self-efficacy
- **At λ↑:** High persistence, strong belief in capability, sustained effort
- **At λ↓:** Giving up easily, learned helplessness, avoidance

### ∂Φ/∂β (Wood Partial)
- **What changes:** Variety of learning pathways, enrichment quality
- **At β↑:** Multiple routes to mastery, rich extensions, creative alternatives
- **At β↓:** Single pathway, boring enrichment, rigid approach

